article.headline: CS-Northridge 64, Long Beach State 56
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Ian Boylan scored 20 points as Cal State Northridge beat Long Beach State 64-56 Thursday night. Cal State's Etoagwara Onyenegecha chipped in 18 points before fouling out and Thomas Shewmake added 12. The Matadors (8-10, 4-6 Big West Conference) have won two of their last three while the 49ers (6-12, 4-5) have lost six of eight. The 49ers pulled within four with 1:20 remaining, but Boylan then hit five straight free throws. He made nine of 12 on the night. Northridge made 13 of 16 free throws as a team, while Long Beach State made just 11 of 25. Cal State Northridge out-rebounded Long Beach State 42 to 31. Onyenegecha and Davin White had eight boards apiece for the Matadors. Long Beach started quickly with a 10-2 lead. Cal State took its first lead at 19-18 on White's layup with 7:17 left in the first half. Northridge eventually went on an 8-0 run to close out the half with a 35-27 lead. Kevin Roberts led the 49ers with 17 points and eight boards. Marcel Jackson had 13 points.
